TITLE: Initializing EAS Configuration with Ethers and EAS SDK in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Sets up the Ethereum provider, signer, and EAS instance using ethers.js and EAS SDK. This function requires RPC URL, registry address, EAS address, and private key inputs. It stores these configurations in the global context for later use.

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Initialize provider with specific network parameters
const provider = new ethers.JsonRpcProvider(msg.rpcUrl)

const signer = new ethers.Wallet(msg.privateKey, provider);

// Initialize EAS with specific gas settings
const EAS = new eassdk.EAS(msg.easAddress);
eas.connect(signer);

// Store in global context
global.set('provider', provider);
global.set('signer', signer);
global.set('eas', eas);
global.set('registryAddress', msg.registryAddress);

msg.payload = 'EAS configuration initialized';
return msg;
```

